<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-12-15T11:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-12-15T11:44:00-05:00" n="680" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d680">
                            <head>No. 678.<lb/><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Sickles</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-12-15T16:30:00-00:14"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 15, 1873—4.30 p.m.</date> (Received 3.20
                                    p.m.)</dateline></opener>
                            <p>President Casteiar called at the legation this afternoon and informed
                                me that the Virginius and survivors had been surrendered to those
                                authorized to receive them on the part of the United States.</p>
                            <closer><signed>SICKLES.</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>